Software Engineer with over 10 years of experience building web applications that users love. I specialize in React, TypeScript, and modern frontend architecture, but I'm equally comfortable diving into backend systems when the project calls for it.

## What I Do

I currently work as a Senior Software Engineer focused on web technologies. My day-to-day involves building scalable frontend applications, mentoring junior developers, and collaborating with product and design teams to turn ideas into polished experiences.

Throughout my career, I've worked across industries including sports media, fintech, and e-commerce. This variety has taught me that while technologies change, the fundamentals of good software engineering remain constant: write readable code, communicate clearly, and always keep the end user in mind.

## Beyond the Code

I'm a firm believer that great engineers are well-rounded humans. When I'm not coding, you'll find me on the volleyball court, basketball court, or tennis court (I'm competitive about my sports). I practice hot yoga to balance out all that intensity, and I'm always planning my next trip to an amusement park—there's nothing quite like a good rollercoaster.

Grew up on the east coast (Baltimore/DC area) and now enjoying the SoCal sunshine. I love a good rooftop happy hour, strategy board games, live music, and road trips to wherever the mood takes me.

## Let's Connect

I'm always interested in hearing about interesting projects, talking shop about frontend architecture, or grabbing coffee with fellow developers. Feel free to reach out.
